<para xmlns="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook" xmlns:xi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XInclude">
  All classes in Java form part of a single-root hierarchy (or
  <quote>tree</quote>), based on the class <literal>java.lang.Object</literal>.
  This is the most abstract view of any object (including arrays), and it
  specifies a number of important services that all objects must provide.
</para>